# Linear MCP Integration

This project uses **Linear** for project and task management, integrated through the **Linear MCP Server**. AI assistants can interact with Linear programmatically to create issues, update projects, manage labels, and more.

## Project Information

- **Workspace:** Laststance
- **Primary Team:** CoreLive
- **Project Management:** Linear is used for tracking features, bugs, and technical debt

## Linear MCP Tools

### Issue Management

#### `list_issues`
List issues in the workspace with flexible filtering.

```typescript
// List all my issues
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  assignee: 'me',
  limit: 50
})

// List issues by team
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  team: 'CoreLive',
  orderBy: 'updatedAt',
  limit: 50
})

// List issues by state
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  state: 'In Progress',
  assignee: 'me'
})

// List issues by label
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  label: 'bug',
  includeArchived: false
})

// List issues by project
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  project: 'Prisma Migration',
  team: 'CoreLive'
})

// Search issues by content
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  query: 'authentication',
  limit: 20
})

// Filter by date
await mcp_linear_list_issues({
  createdAt: '-P1D', // Created in the last day
  updatedAt: '-P1W'  // Updated in the last week
})
```

**Parameters:**
- `assignee`: User ID, name, email, or `"me"`
- `team`: Team name or ID
- `state`: State name or ID
- `label`: Label name or ID
- `project`: Project name or ID
- `cycle`: Cycle name or ID
- `query`: Search in title/description
- `includeArchived`: Default `true`
- `limit`: Max 250, default 50
- `orderBy`: `"createdAt"` or `"updatedAt"` (default)

#### `get_issue`
Get detailed issue information including attachments and git branch name.

```typescript
const issue = await mcp_linear_get_issue({
  id: 'COR-123'
})
```

**Returns:**
- Full issue details including description, comments, attachments, labels, assignee, project, cycle, git branch name, etc.

#### `create_issue`
Create a new Linear issue.

```typescript
await mcp_linear_create_issue({
  title: 'Migrate Prisma from v6 to v7',
  team: 'CoreLive',
  description: '## Objective\n\nUpgrade Prisma ORM to v7...',
  assignee: 'me',
  state: 'In Progress',
  priority: 2, // 0=No priority, 1=Urgent, 2=High, 3=Normal, 4=Low
  labels: ['technical-debt', 'database'],
  project: 'Infrastructure Upgrades',
  dueDate: '2025-12-31',
  links: [
    {
      url: 'https://www.prisma.io/docs/orm/more/upgrade-guides/upgrading-versions/upgrading-to-prisma-7',
      title: 'Prisma 7 Upgrade Guide'
    }
  ]
})
```

**Parameters:**
- `title`: **Required** - Issue title
- `team`: **Required** - Team name or ID
- `description`: Markdown description
- `assignee`: User ID, name, email, or `"me"`
- `state`: State type, name, or ID
- `priority`: 0-4 (only set if explicitly requested)
- `labels`: Array of label names or IDs
- `project`: Project name or ID
- `cycle`: Cycle name, number, or ID
- `parentId`: Parent issue ID for sub-issues
- `dueDate`: ISO format date
- `links`: Array of `{ url, title }` objects

#### `update_issue`
Update an existing issue.

```typescript
await mcp_linear_update_issue({
  id: 'COR-123',
  state: 'Done',
  description: 'Updated description...',
  labels: ['completed', 'v7-migration']
})
```

**Parameters:** Same as `create_issue`, plus `id` (required)

